Gamesa Wins New Sri Lanka Order to Raise Capacity by Half

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-06-15T10:01:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/gamesa-wins-new-sri-lanka-order-to-raise-capacity-by-half.html
Gamesa Corp Tecnologica SA (GAM) , Europe’s
second-largest wind turbine-maker, will boost its installed
capacity in  Sri Lanka  by half with a new order for a 10.2-
megawatt project in the country.  The company’s India unit will deliver 12 of the G58, 850-
kilowatt turbines to Pawan Danavi Pvt. by the third quarter,
Gamesa said in an e-mailed statement.  The project will raise Gamesa’s installed capacity in Sri
Lanka to 30.2 megawatts, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  